The NODES define the bounds of interval of definition of the
B-SPLINE parameter and determine the segments on which
each component (2 in 2d, 3 in 3d) of the B-SPLINE line
is a polynomial or rational function.
The input of a node is a REAL.

The number of nodes of the OPENED B-SPLINE is equal to
the number of points + degree of polynomials + 1.

The number of nodes of the CLOSED B-SPLINE is equal to
the number of points and is not demanded.

The node may be repeated but a node repeated 3 times
will be count 3 for this number.

Example: 10; { 10 nodes }
         0;0;0; 1;1; 2.2; 3; 5;5;5; {values of 10 nodes}

The length of segments (between 2 distinct nodes) induces
to the form of the B-SPLINE CURVE.
